{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":904,"text":"Hello, everybody."},{"time":2333,"text":"I brought with me today a baby diaper."},{"time":6793,"text":"You'll see why in a second."},{"time":8539,"text":"Baby diapers have interesting properties."},{"time":10573,"text":"They can swell enormously\nwhen you add water to them,"},{"time":13288,"text":"an experiment done\nby millions of kids every day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":16296,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":17470,"text":"But the reason why"},{"time":18988,"text":"is that they're designed\nin a very clever way."},{"time":21202,"text":"They're made out of a thing\ncalled a swellable material."},{"time":23861,"text":"It's a special kind of material that,\nwhen you add water,"},{"time":26622,"text":"it will swell up enormously,"},{"time":28076,"text":"maybe a thousand times in volume."},{"time":30266,"text":"And this is a very useful,\nindustrial kind of polymer."},{"time":33819,"text":"But what we're trying to do\nin my group at MIT"},{"time":36369,"text":"is to figure out if we can do\nsomething similar to the brain."},{"time":39606,"text":"Can we make it bigger,"},{"time":40789,"text":"big enough that you\ncan peer inside"},{"time":42481,"text":"and see all the tiny building blocks,\nthe biomolecules,"},{"time":45133,"text":"how they're organized in three dimensions,"},{"time":47308,"text":"the structure, the ground truth\nstructure of the brain, if you will?"},{"time":50817,"text":"If we could get that,"},{"time":51999,"text":"maybe we could have a better understanding\nof how the brain is organized"},{"time":55532,"text":"to yield thoughts and emotions"},{"time":57215,"text":"and actions and sensations."},{"time":58958,"text":"Maybe we could try to pinpoint\nthe exact changes in the brain"},{"time":62397,"text":"that result in diseases,"},{"time":64197,"text":"diseases like Alzheimer's\nand epilepsy and Parkinson's,"},{"time":67433,"text":"for which there are few\ntreatments, much less cures,"},{"time":70035,"text":"and for which, very often,\nwe don't know the cause or the origins"},{"time":73676,"text":"and what's really causing them to occur."},{"time":76613,"text":"Now, our group at MIT"},{"time":78377,"text":"is trying to take\na different point of view"},{"time":81087,"text":"from the way neuroscience has\nbeen done over the last hundred years."},{"time":84341,"text":"We're designers. We're inventors."},{"time":85944,"text":"We're trying to figure out\nhow to build technologies"},{"time":88512,"text":"that let us look at and repair the brain."},{"time":90992,"text":"And the reason is,"},{"time":92167,"text":"the brain is incredibly,\nincredibly complicated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":95484,"text":"So what we've learned\nover the first century of neuroscience"},{"time":98395,"text":"is that the brain is a very\ncomplicated network,"},{"time":100722,"text":"made out of very specialized\ncells called neurons"},{"time":103226,"text":"with very complex geometries,"},{"time":104917,"text":"and electrical currents will flow\nthrough these complexly shaped neurons."},{"time":109653,"text":"Furthermore, neurons\nare connected in networks."},{"time":112461,"text":"They're connected by little junctions\ncalled synapses that exchange chemicals"},{"time":116320,"text":"and allow the neurons\nto talk to each other."},{"time":118562,"text":"The density of the brain is incredible."},{"time":120526,"text":"In a cubic millimeter of your brain,"},{"time":122857,"text":"there are about 100,000 of these neurons"},{"time":125338,"text":"and maybe a billion of those connections."},{"time":128887,"text":"But it's worse."},{"time":130293,"text":"So, if you could zoom in to a neuron,"},{"time":132622,"text":"and, of course, this is just\nour artist's rendition of it."},{"time":135396,"text":"What you would see are thousands\nand thousands of kinds of biomolecules,"},{"time":139627,"text":"little nanoscale machines\norganized in complex, 3D patterns,"},{"time":144051,"text":"and together they mediate\nthose electrical pulses,"},{"time":146703,"text":"those chemical exchanges\nthat allow neurons to work together"},{"time":150664,"text":"to generate things like thoughts\nand feelings and so forth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154357,"text":"Now, we don't know how\nthe neurons in the brain are organized"},{"time":158145,"text":"to form networks,"},{"time":159343,"text":"and we don't know how\nthe biomolecules are organized"},{"time":161867,"text":"within neurons"},{"time":163065,"text":"to form these complex, organized machines."},{"time":165918,"text":"If we really want to understand this,"},{"time":167762,"text":"we're going to need new technologies."},{"time":169603,"text":"But if we could get such maps,"},{"time":171411,"text":"if we could look at the organization\nof molecules and neurons"},{"time":174378,"text":"and neurons and networks,"},{"time":175968,"text":"maybe we could really understand\nhow the brain conducts information"},{"time":179429,"text":"from sensory regions,"},{"time":180620,"text":"mixes it with emotion and feeling,"},{"time":182380,"text":"and generates our decisions and actions."},{"time":185131,"text":"Maybe we could pinpoint the exact set\nof molecular changes that occur"},{"time":188944,"text":"in a brain disorder."},{"time":190170,"text":"And once we know how\nthose molecules have changed,"},{"time":193016,"text":"whether they've increased in number\nor changed in pattern,"},{"time":195820,"text":"we could use those\nas targets for new drugs,"},{"time":198783,"text":"for new ways of delivering\nenergy into the brain"},{"time":201078,"text":"in order to repair the brain\ncomputations that are afflicted"},{"time":204982,"text":"in patients who suffer\nfrom brain disorders."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207793,"text":"We've all seen lots of different\ntechnologies over the last century"},{"time":211060,"text":"to try to confront this."},{"time":212250,"text":"I think we've all seen brain scans"},{"time":214154,"text":"taken using MRI machines."},{"time":216212,"text":"These, of course, have the great power\nthat they are noninvasive,"},{"time":219583,"text":"they can be used on living human subjects."},{"time":222407,"text":"But also, they're spatially crude."},{"time":224662,"text":"Each of these blobs that you see,\nor voxels, as they're called,"},{"time":227676,"text":"can contain millions\nand millions of neurons."},{"time":230389,"text":"So it's not at the level of resolution"},{"time":232263,"text":"where it can pinpoint\nthe molecular changes that occur"},{"time":234825,"text":"or the changes in the wiring\nof these networks"},{"time":237135,"text":"that contributes to our ability\nto be conscious and powerful beings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241797,"text":"At the other extreme,\nyou have microscopes."},{"time":245002,"text":"Microscopes, of course, will use light\nto look at little tiny things."},{"time":248321,"text":"For centuries, they've been used\nto look at things like bacteria."},{"time":251420,"text":"For neuroscience,"},{"time":252595,"text":"microscopes are actually how neurons\nwere discovered in the first place,"},{"time":256031,"text":"about 130 years ago."},{"time":257347,"text":"But light is fundamentally limited."},{"time":259689,"text":"You can't see individual molecules\nwith a regular old microscope."},{"time":263011,"text":"You can't look at these tiny connections."},{"time":265187,"text":"So if we want to make our ability\nto see the brain more powerful,"},{"time":269153,"text":"to get down to the ground truth structure,"},{"time":271345,"text":"we're going to need to have\neven better technologies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":275611,"text":"My group, a couple years ago,\nstarted thinking:"},{"time":277859,"text":"Why don't we do the opposite?"},{"time":279295,"text":"If it's so darn complicated\nto zoom in to the brain,"},{"time":281780,"text":"why can't we make the brain bigger?"},{"time":284166,"text":"It initially started"},{"time":285345,"text":"with two grad students in my group,\nFei Chen and Paul Tillberg."},{"time":288365,"text":"Now many others in my group\nare helping with this process."},{"time":291109,"text":"We decided to try to figure out\nif we could take polymers,"},{"time":293895,"text":"like the stuff in the baby diaper,"},{"time":295548,"text":"and install it physically\nwithin the brain."},{"time":297578,"text":"If we could do it just right,\nand you add water,"},{"time":299843,"text":"you can potentially blow the brain up"},{"time":301702,"text":"to where you could distinguish\nthose tiny biomolecules from each other."},{"time":305103,"text":"You would see those connections\nand get maps of the brain."},{"time":307997,"text":"This could potentially be quite dramatic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310009,"text":"We brought a little demo here."},{"time":313538,"text":"We got some purified baby diaper material."},{"time":316137,"text":"It's much easier\njust to buy it off the Internet"},{"time":318435,"text":"than to extract the few grains\nthat actually occur in these diapers."},{"time":321934,"text":"I'm going to put just one teaspoon here"},{"time":324706,"text":"of this purified polymer."},{"time":327270,"text":"And here we have some water."},{"time":329446,"text":"What we're going to do"},{"time":330632,"text":"is see if this teaspoon\nof the baby diaper material"},{"time":333667,"text":"can increase in size."},{"time":336687,"text":"You're going to see it increase in volume\nby about a thousandfold"},{"time":340407,"text":"before your very eyes."},{"time":349597,"text":"I could pour much more of this in there,"},{"time":351593,"text":"but I think you've got the idea"},{"time":353175,"text":"that this is a very,\nvery interesting molecule,"},{"time":355701,"text":"and if can use it in the right way,"},{"time":357637,"text":"we might be able\nto really zoom in on the brain"},{"time":359982,"text":"in a way that you can't do\nwith past technologies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363227,"text":"OK. So a little bit of chemistry now."},{"time":365305,"text":"What's going on\nin the baby diaper polymer?"},{"time":367771,"text":"If you could zoom in,"},{"time":369471,"text":"it might look something like\nwhat you see on the screen."},{"time":372168,"text":"Polymers are chains of atoms\narranged in long, thin lines."},{"time":376684,"text":"The chains are very tiny,"},{"time":378075,"text":"about the width of a biomolecule,"},{"time":379963,"text":"and these polymers are really dense."},{"time":381734,"text":"They're separated by distances"},{"time":383258,"text":"that are around the size of a biomolecule."},{"time":385534,"text":"This is very good"},{"time":386723,"text":"because we could potentially\nmove everything apart in the brain."},{"time":389788,"text":"If we add water, what will happen is,"},{"time":391660,"text":"this swellable material\nis going to absorb the water,"},{"time":394199,"text":"the polymer chains will move\napart from each other,"},{"time":396623,"text":"and the entire material\nis going to become bigger."},{"time":399615,"text":"And because these chains are so tiny"},{"time":401453,"text":"and spaced by biomolecular distances,"},{"time":403682,"text":"we could potentially blow up the brain"},{"time":405745,"text":"and make it big enough to see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408020,"text":"Here's the mystery, then:"},{"time":409284,"text":"How do we actually make\nthese polymer chains inside the brain"},{"time":412918,"text":"so we can move all the biomolecules apart?"},{"time":415181,"text":"If we could do that,"},{"time":416356,"text":"maybe we could get\nground truth maps of the brain."},{"time":418777,"text":"We could look at the wiring."},{"time":420190,"text":"We can peer inside\nand see the molecules within."},{"time":423925,"text":"To explain this, we made some animations"},{"time":426430,"text":"where we actually look\nat, in these artist renderings,"},{"time":429057,"text":"what biomolecules might look\nlike and how we might separate them."},{"time":432622,"text":"Step one: what we'd have\nto do, first of all,"},{"time":435195,"text":"is attach every biomolecule,\nshown in brown here,"},{"time":438608,"text":"to a little anchor, a little handle."},{"time":440791,"text":"We need to pull the molecules\nof the brain apart from each other,"},{"time":443910,"text":"and to do that, we need\nto have a little handle"},{"time":446260,"text":"that allows those polymers to bind to them"},{"time":448569,"text":"and to exert their force."}]},{"cues":[{"time":451278,"text":"Now, if you just take baby diaper\npolymer and dump it on the brain,"},{"time":454463,"text":"obviously, it's going to sit there on top."},{"time":456524,"text":"So we need to find a way\nto make the polymers inside."},{"time":459076,"text":"And this is where we're really lucky."},{"time":460888,"text":"It turns out, you can\nget the building blocks,"},{"time":463100,"text":"monomers, as they're called,"},{"time":464496,"text":"and if you let them go into the brain"},{"time":466304,"text":"and then trigger the chemical reactions,"},{"time":468364,"text":"you can get them to form\nthose long chains,"},{"time":471090,"text":"right there inside the brain tissue."},{"time":473325,"text":"They're going to wind their way\naround biomolecules"},{"time":475746,"text":"and between biomolecules,"},{"time":476991,"text":"forming those complex webs"},{"time":478640,"text":"that will allow you, eventually,\nto pull apart the molecules"},{"time":481526,"text":"from each other."},{"time":482725,"text":"And every time one\nof those little handles is around,"},{"time":485803,"text":"the polymer will bind to the handle,\nand that's exactly what we need"},{"time":489177,"text":"in order to pull the molecules\napart from each other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":491732,"text":"All right, the moment of truth."},{"time":493449,"text":"We have to treat this specimen"},{"time":495621,"text":"with a chemical to kind of loosen up\nall the molecules from each other,"},{"time":499091,"text":"and then, when we add water,"},{"time":500951,"text":"that swellable material is going\nto start absorbing the water,"},{"time":503928,"text":"the polymer chains will move apart,"},{"time":505655,"text":"but now, the biomolecules\nwill come along for the ride."},{"time":508401,"text":"And much like drawing\na picture on a balloon,"},{"time":510589,"text":"and then you blow up the balloon,"},{"time":512200,"text":"the image is the same,"},{"time":513514,"text":"but the ink particles have moved\naway from each other."},{"time":516086,"text":"And that's what we've been able\nto do now, but in three dimensions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519577,"text":"There's one last trick."},{"time":521600,"text":"As you can see here,"},{"time":522842,"text":"we've color-coded\nall the biomolecules brown."},{"time":524975,"text":"That's because they all\nkind of look the same."},{"time":527169,"text":"Biomolecules are made\nout of the same atoms,"},{"time":529298,"text":"but just in different orders."},{"time":531562,"text":"So we need one last thing"},{"time":533086,"text":"in order to make them visible."},{"time":534805,"text":"We have to bring in little tags,"},{"time":536408,"text":"with glowing dyes\nthat will distinguish them."},{"time":539451,"text":"So one kind of biomolecule\nmight get a blue color."},{"time":542148,"text":"Another kind of biomolecule\nmight get a red color."},{"time":544523,"text":"And so forth."},{"time":545823,"text":"And that's the final step."},{"time":547399,"text":"Now we can look at something like a brain"},{"time":549701,"text":"and look at the individual molecules,"},{"time":551521,"text":"because we've moved them\nfar apart enough from each other"},{"time":554252,"text":"that we can tell them apart."}]},{"cues":[{"time":555974,"text":"So the hope here is that\nwe can make the invisible visible."},{"time":558832,"text":"We can turn things that might seem\nsmall and obscure"},{"time":561422,"text":"and blow them up"},{"time":562597,"text":"until they're like constellations\nof information about life."},{"time":565798,"text":"Here's an actual video\nof what it might look like."},{"time":568197,"text":"We have here a little brain in a dish --"},{"time":570592,"text":"a little piece of a brain, actually."},{"time":572363,"text":"We've infused the polymer in,"},{"time":573983,"text":"and now we're adding water."},{"time":575474,"text":"What you'll see is that,\nright before your eyes --"},{"time":577856,"text":"this video is sped up about sixtyfold --"},{"time":579803,"text":"this little piece of brain tissue\nis going to grow."},{"time":582552,"text":"It can increase by a hundredfold\nor even more in volume."},{"time":585756,"text":"And the cool part is, because\nthose polymers are so tiny,"},{"time":588729,"text":"we're separating biomolecules\nevenly from each other."},{"time":591312,"text":"It's a smooth expansion."},{"time":592994,"text":"We're not losing the configuration\nof the information."},{"time":595705,"text":"We're just making it easier to see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":599333,"text":"So now we can take\nactual brain circuitry --"},{"time":601533,"text":"here's a piece of the brain\ninvolved with, for example, memory --"},{"time":604691,"text":"and we can zoom in."},{"time":605978,"text":"We can start to actually look at\nhow circuits are configured."},{"time":608892,"text":"Maybe someday we could read out a memory."},{"time":610884,"text":"Maybe we could actually look\nat how circuits are configured"},{"time":613687,"text":"to process emotions,"},{"time":614863,"text":"how the actual wiring\nof our brain is organized"},{"time":617809,"text":"in order to make us who we are."},{"time":620400,"text":"And of course, we can pinpoint, hopefully,"},{"time":622471,"text":"the actual problems in the brain\nat a molecular level."},{"time":625654,"text":"What if we could actually\nlook into cells in the brain"},{"time":628247,"text":"and figure out, wow, here are the 17\nmolecules that have altered"},{"time":631354,"text":"in this brain tissue that has been\nundergoing epilepsy"},{"time":634833,"text":"or changing in Parkinson's disease"},{"time":636507,"text":"or otherwise being altered?"},{"time":638048,"text":"If we get that systematic list\nof things that are going wrong,"},{"time":641115,"text":"those become our therapeutic targets."},{"time":643338,"text":"We can build drugs that bind those."},{"time":645039,"text":"We can maybe aim energy\nat different parts of the brain"},{"time":647690,"text":"in order to help people\nwith Parkinson's or epilepsy"},{"time":650401,"text":"or other conditions that affect\nover a billion people"},{"time":652976,"text":"around the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":655246,"text":"Now, something interesting\nhas been happening."},{"time":657476,"text":"It turns out that throughout biomedicine,"},{"time":660205,"text":"there are other problems\nthat expansion might help with."},{"time":662895,"text":"This is an actual biopsy\nfrom a human breast cancer patient."},{"time":666505,"text":"It turns out that if you look at cancers,"},{"time":668717,"text":"if you look at the immune system,"},{"time":670352,"text":"if you look at aging,\nif you look at development --"},{"time":672889,"text":"all these processes are involving\nlarge-scale biological systems."},{"time":677410,"text":"But of course, the problems begin\nwith those little nanoscale molecules,"},{"time":681458,"text":"the machines that make the cells\nand the organs in our body tick."},{"time":685351,"text":"So what we're trying\nto do now is to figure out"},{"time":687597,"text":"if we can actually use this technology\nto map the building blocks of life"},{"time":691087,"text":"in a wide variety of diseases."},{"time":692856,"text":"Can we actually pinpoint\nthe molecular changes in a tumor"},{"time":695776,"text":"so that we can actually\ngo after it in a smart way"},{"time":698169,"text":"and deliver drugs that might wipe out\nexactly the cells that we want to?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":702137,"text":"You know, a lot of medicine\nis very high risk."},{"time":704496,"text":"Sometimes, it's even guesswork."},{"time":706626,"text":"My hope is we can actually turn\nwhat might be a high-risk moon shot"},{"time":710525,"text":"into something that's more reliable."},{"time":712318,"text":"If you think about the original moon shot,"},{"time":714397,"text":"where they actually landed on the moon,"},{"time":716319,"text":"it was based on solid science."},{"time":717787,"text":"We understood gravity;"},{"time":719414,"text":"we understood aerodynamics."},{"time":720779,"text":"We knew how to build rockets."},{"time":722198,"text":"The science risk was under control."},{"time":724690,"text":"It was still a great, great\nfeat of engineering."},{"time":727467,"text":"But in medicine, we don't\nnecessarily have all the laws."},{"time":730136,"text":"Do we have all the laws\nthat are analogous to gravity,"},{"time":733269,"text":"that are analogous to aerodynamics?"},{"time":735637,"text":"I would argue that with technologies"},{"time":737391,"text":"like the kinds I'm talking about today,"},{"time":739287,"text":"maybe we can actually derive those."},{"time":741004,"text":"We can map the patterns\nthat occur in living systems,"},{"time":743885,"text":"and figure out how to overcome\nthe diseases that plague us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":749499,"text":"You know, my wife and I\nhave two young kids,"},{"time":751602,"text":"and one of my hopes as a bioengineer\nis to make life better for them"},{"time":754860,"text":"than it currently is for us."},{"time":756613,"text":"And my hope is, if we can\nturn biology and medicine"},{"time":760367,"text":"from these high-risk endeavors\nthat are governed by chance and luck,"},{"time":764748,"text":"and make them things\nthat we win by skill and hard work,"},{"time":768699,"text":"then that would be a great advance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":770621,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":771851,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}